      "text": " I'll help create a visual representation of these notebook pages while maintaining their content and structure in a more organized format.\n\n\n\n```\ngraph TD\n    subgraph \"Page 1 - Road Map [Ref: 1.0]\"\n        A1[7 Seas Unite - Golden Aire Community]\n        B1[Wed. before Thanksgiving Potluck Friends Giving Platform]\n        \n        subgraph \"Activities/Areas [Ref: 1.1]\"\n            C1[Swaylo?]\n            D1[Cannabis brands]\n            E1[Mushroom brands]\n            F1[Fashion brands]\n            G1[Interactive Art Spaces]\n            H1[Class to be held Prior - during]\n            I1[Podcast area - outside]\n            J1[Pri opening ceremony]\n            K1[Sand bowls]\n        end\n        \n        subgraph \"Entertainment [Ref: 1.2]\"\n            L1[Jim sesh - bring instruments]\n            M1[Circus Acts - Pablo - magicians]\n            N1[Dauray -> Circus people]\n        end\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Page 2 - Seven Wonders of the World [Ref: 2.0]\"\n        A2[Fashion Line]\n        \n        subgraph \"Regions [Ref: 2.1]\"\n            B2[Europe - Renai sconc]\n            C2[USA - Prohibida/Hip Hop]\n            D2[Asian Cultural]\n            E2[African - Tunisian/Egypt/Morr]\n            F2[South America - Ecuador/Costa Rica]\n            G2[India]\n            H2[Australia - Outback]\n            I2[UK - Nymia]\n        end\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Page 3 - Geographic Areas [Ref: 3.0]\"\n        A3[Europe - London]\n        B3[Australia - Fashion Shows]\n        C3[Asia - Model Lynn]\n        D3[Africa]\n        \n        subgraph \"Big Gigantic [Ref: 3.1]\"\n            E3[Place 8PM]\n        end\n    end\n```\n\nI've recreated the notebook pages with reference numbers to help organize the information. Each major section has a reference number (e.g., 1.0, 2.0, 3.0) and subsections are numbered accordingly (e.g., 1.1, 1.2). The diagram maintains the original content while providing a clearer structure.\n\nK